<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-06-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-06-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="752" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d752">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Choate</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-06-22"><hi rend="italic">June 22,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hay states that Mr. Geldart says his shipment by the <hi rend="italic">Mashona</hi>, including necessary charges, would be
                            covered by $1,000, and that $575 would cover his shipment by the <hi rend="italic">Beatrice</hi>. If better terms can not be had,
                            however, he will accept the British offer.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>